                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/oo/edit/master/knpu/episode2/one-db-conn-with-property.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>I can't stand it any longer. The app is small, but our database credentials
are already duplicated <em>and</em> hidden inside this one class. What if we added
a second table - like <code>battle</code> - and a <code>BattleLoader</code> class? At this rate,
we'd be copying and pasting the database password <em>there</em> too. Gross.</p>
<h2 id="isolate-the-pdo-creation-in-shiploader">Isolate the PDO Creation in ShipLoader <a class="headerlink" href="one-db-conn-with-property#isolate-the-pdo-creation-in-shiploader" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Enough is enough. Let's fix this little by little. First, I don't want to
duplicate the <code>new PDO</code> code twice in this class. To fix that, create a
<code>private function getPDO()</code> - private because - at least so far - we only
want to call this from inside <code>ShipLoader</code>. Copy the <code>new PDO</code> line and
the one below it and put them here. Return <code>$pdo</code> and let's even add some
nice PHPDoc:</p>
