</p>
<p>Now, we can use a little trick thanks to OO! Down in <code>getPDO()</code>, add an <code>if</code>
statement to check if the <code>pdo</code> property is equal to <code>null</code>. Why of course
it is! So far, nothing is setting it, so it's <em>always</em> null. But now, if
it <em>is</em> null, move the <code>new PDO()</code> code into this and then assign this to
the <code>pdo</code> property. Finish by returning <code>$this-&gt;pdo</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="55958e3bbc">
